Package supermart.backEnd

Class Item

  • java.lang.Object
    • supermart.backEnd.Item

  • public class Item
extends java.lang.Object
    Author:
    Harrison Berryman - 09745092 Builds an item object for use in stock.

    Builds an item object with a name, cost, price, reorder point, reorder amount and temperature (for non-dry items).

    • Constructor Detail

      • Item

        public Item​(java.lang.String name,
            double cost,
            double price,
            int reorderPoint,
            int reorderAmount,
            double temperature)
        An item constructor for non-dry items with a temperature

        Constructs an item based on the parameters provided, including a temperature that the item must be kept at when being shipped in a truck.

        Parameters:
        name - The name of the item e.g. "fish"
        cost - The cost of the item when purchased by the store
        price - The price of the item the store sells it at
        reorderPoint - When the item's quantity reaches this point it is reordered
        reorderAmount - When an item is reordered, this is the amount reordered
        temperature - The minimum temperature the item must be kept at when in a truck

      • Item

            int reorderPoint,

        An item constructor for dry objects that have no temperature

        Constructs an item based on the parameters provided.

        Parameters:
        name - The name of the item e.g. "corn"
        cost - The cost of the item when purchased by the store
        price - The price of the item the store sells it at
        reorderPoint - The quantity the item must reach before it's reordered
        reorderAmount - The quantity of items reordered whenever the reorderPoint is reached

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString​()
        Returns a string of the item's name and all other parameters

        Expected string should be "itemName, itemCost, itemPrice, reorderPoint, reorderAmount" If the item is not dry it should also include temperature at the end.

        This is done for use in the GUI and when converted to a CSV.

        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        A string of the Item's details including temperature if the item is non-dry.

      • GetTemperature

        public double GetTemperature​()
                      throws DryException
        Returns the temperature of the item, throws exception if item is dry

        Used to return the current temperature of the item, first isDry is checked to determine if the item is dry, if it is a DryException is thrown as there is no temperature to return.

        Returns:
        The item's temperature if the item is non-dry
        Throws:
        DryException - If the item is dry, to prevent errors
